          "mode": 0,
          "value": "saveDC=15,\nlabel=Corroded,\nsaveAbility=dex|con,\nsaveRemove=true,\nrollType=check,\nchatFlavor=This shit sticky yo,\nactionSave=dialog,",
          "priority": 20
        }
      ],
      "description": "<p><strong>Max Ranks</strong>: 5</p><hr /><p>A <strong>Corroded</strong> creature has been exposed to some kind of acidic compound, causing their flesh and equipment to wither and deteriorate if left untreated.</p><ul><li><p>A <strong>Corroded</strong> creature gains a -2 penalty to its DR (damage reduction) for each rank it has.</p></li><li><p>A <strong>Corroded</strong> creature gains a -1 penalty to all Constitution based checks &amp; saves for each rank it has.</p></li><li><p>A creature can end the corroded condition by using their action making a DC 15 Dexterity or Constitution Ability Check or submerging themselves fully into a body of water.</p></li></ul>",
